Website: <a href=" http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/tvradio/programmes/lifeincoldblood/index.shtml" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/tvradio/programmes/lifeincoldblood/index.shtml</a>

New series. David Attenborough reveals the surprising truth about the cold-blooded lives
of reptiles and amphibians, who are as dramatic in combat, as colourful in their communication
and as tender in their parental care as any other animal.

Featuring giant courting crocodiles, tortoises that joust with lances and bright
red sumo-wrestling frogs, who all live their lives to the full.
